5:
Thank you for speaking to me today.
Is there anything else bothering you?
9:
I see. Thank you. I hope we run into
each other again sometime.
13: Emilia, what are you doing here?
18: It seems she is talking to strangers.
22:
It was just a short chat. I'm
researching problems experienced
by drifters.
24:
My friends and I were lucky enough
to run into all of you, but not
everyone is so fortunate, correct?
27:
I have heard some drifters are even
children, so I want to help them if I
can...
36:
I'm not doing anything special. I just
can't bear to see anyone in need
suffering.
39:
This is the information I've gathered
so far. Based on this, I think I'll be
creating a proposal for the Guild.
44:
Yeah, from what's written here, it
sounds like the drifters are really
struggling. We had no idea...
48:
That reminds me, could I also ask for
your help?
50:
Hearing your own stories and
having an outside opinion will surely
help me write a good proposal.
55:
Of course. You have our full
cooperation.
59:
W-well, what do you think? If you
notice any issues, please tell me.
63:
Whoa, this looks great! Couldn't you
submit this as is?
68:
I agree! You've already compiled the
support strategies you wish to
implement and their merits into a
very easy-to-read format.
72:
Are you sure this is good enough? I
feel like it's missing something.
76:
So if you were to receive a report like
this, you would not be satisfied,
correct?
81:
Correct... Perhaps I should add
information on how the surrounding
allied countries are handling this
situation.
83:
Just because something would work
for Palpebra doesn't mean it works
for them, after all.
85:
Especially since there are a few
places that think ill of drifters and
Palpebra.
90:
Oh... Politics, huh? You're right. That
could be an issue...
93:
Ah, in that case, how about wording
it like this?
97:
...In order to help solve the issues I've
just mentioned, we would like to
submit this proposal to aid the
drifters.
101:
Gotcha! I was wondering why you
wanted to talk so bad. Who knew it'd
be about business.
105:
I think it would be best for the Guild
to collect and manage information
on the drifters' skills.
109:
True. That might lead us to meeting
more people like Alk and the others!
114:
All that knowledge would serve to
educate the Guild members as well,
leading to more skilled personnel.
116:
With their newly acquired skills and
knowledge, the range of jobs the
Guild could accept would expand
and
122:
That's all I need to hear! You've got
yourselves a deal!
127:
Huh?! B-but I haven't finished my
presentation.
132:
No biggie! I got the gist of it from
that explanation of yours.
134:
I was already aware that some
drifters were struggling, so I'm really
glad you brought this proposal to
me.
143:
Y-yes, it is... I'm just surprised
negotiations finished so quickly.
148:
This is just another result of your
hard work. Stand tall and proud of
what you've accomplished, Emilia.
153:
Thank you! I couldn't have done this
without all your help.
158:
Ah, just to be clear, we're not gonna
do everything listed here right away.
We'll start with the easiest to
implement.
161:
If everything goes well, then we'll
start expanding the program!
166:
Think we could lend a hand? I don't
remember any rules saying you
couldn't have outside help.
171:
Of course you can! I was actually
hoping you'd say something. Can't
start a new project without our
workhorses.
177:
We're happy to help, but I'm not sure
I like that phrasing...
183:
Thank you again. I'm so glad I asked
you all for help.
187:
Don't thank us yet. We still have a lot
of work to do going forward,
especially if we want all your plans
to be put into action.
190:
May I ask what sparked this sudden
desire to help the drifters? All this
has little to do with returning you to
your original world.
195:
I just want to do everything I can to
achieve my goals.
197:
I've been focused on finding a way
home, but actually, there's a lot I
can learn here in Palpebra.
202:
I see. So you're simply learning new
skills that could prove useful upon
your return to your own world.
206:
Exactly. I'm trying to focus on doing
what I can and worrying less about
what I can't.
211:
Oh, if it isn't Mili. About to head out
with Alk and everyone?
215:
No, we just got back. Thanks to our
friends, everything went off without
a hitch.
220:
You know, Mili, it's nice to see you
happy again.
224: Huh? Did I seem sad before?
229:
Yes, but now we always see you
smiling.
234:
Yeah, giving yourself a bit of a slack
has really paid off!
238:
Well, if that's the case, then it is no
doubt thanks to you and our friends.
242:
...I finally understand that I don't
need to shoulder everything alone.
Thank you.
245:
I'll work even harder to make my
dreams a reality!
